race.comment: INSAIN HARRY (2) is fresh from a spell of five months and did hit the frame when last resuming at Kyneton over 1103m. Fitter for a minor placing in a recent Flemington trial. Expecting a bright start for the new stable. ZUBBA STORM (6) is in great hands and showed good early speed last start on debut and fought on well to hold third, beaten 3.5 lengths, over 1100m at Moe. Open to improvement and looks a serious contender. HEXED (13) will be better for the debut outing, when she was beaten a long way but the winner of that race might be pretty smart. She'd trialled well before that so happy to give another chance. FORWARD HO (7) is the lone debutant in the race and while you probably would have liked to see more at the jumpouts, there's not a lot of depth to this so any significant market moves need to be respected.
